%20that%20being%20well-liked%20at%20work%20can%20impact%20performance%20and%20promotions%2C%20but%20isn't%20essential.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDoolin%20shares%20how%20to%20tell%20if%20your%20peers%20like%20you%2C%20and%20why%20collegiate%20workplaces%20can%20help%20productivity.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Michael%20Doolin%2C%20CEO%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cloverhr.co.uk%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EClover%20HR%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3E%20and%20former%20human%20resources%20director%20at%20PwC%2C%20British%20Airways%2C%20and%20DPD%20in%20Ireland.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEmployees%20probably%20think%20about%20being%20liked%20at%20work%20more%20than%20they%20care%20to%20admit.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESubtle%20hints%2C%20like%20a%20boss%20inviting%20someone%20out%20to%20lunch%20or%20enquiring%20more%20about%20others%20than%20themselves%2C%20can%20generate%20stress%2C%20anxiety%2C%20or%20insecurity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt's%20not%20necessary%20to%20be%20liked%20by%20your%20manager%20or%20your%20colleagues%20if%20you're%20doing%20your%20job%20right%2C%20but%20it%20certainly%20helps.%20It%20will%20make%20your%20life%20easier%20and%20more%20enjoyable.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBeing%20liked%20and%20respected%20are%20different%20things.%20Signs%20that%20an%20employee%20is%20well-liked%20include%20people%20sharing%20their%20mistakes%20and%20successes%20with%20that%20person%2C%20whereas%20an%20employee%20is%20respected%20if%20they're%20asked%20to%20resolve%20issues%2C%20for%20advice%2C%20or%20share%20their%20thoughts%20on%20the%20future.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBeing%20well-liked%20and%20respected%20can%20help%20employees%20get%20promoted%2C%20but%20gaining%20respect%20is%20more%20important.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20not%20everything%20at%20work%20boils%20down%20to%20performance.%20Having%20a%20team%20with%20strong%20connections%20can%20significantly%20impact%20productivity%20and%20morale.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECamaraderie%20creates%20a%20work%20environment%20where%20workers%20feel%20comfortable%20sharing%20ideas%2C%20which%20can%20lead%20to%20greater%20innovation%20and%20problem-solving.%20Engaged%2C%20motivated%2C%20and%20effective%20employees%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20advance%20within%20the%20company.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20are%20some%20common%20signs%20that%20you're%20liked%20%E2%80%94%20and%20respected%20%E2%80%94%20at%20work.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227c38f826-244e-488b-9814-33dbbc139348%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou're%20being%20included%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20you're%20being%20encouraged%20to%20participate%20in%20projects%20or%20being%20asked%20to%20undertake%20jobs%2C%20new%20assignments%2C%20or%20tasks%20on%20behalf%20of%20your%20manager%2C%20it's%20a%20subtle%20hint%20that%20you're%20liked%20and%20respected.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEqually%2C%20being%20asked%20to%20attend%20meetings%20and%20events%2C%20both%20social%20and%20professional%2C%20is%20a%20sign%20that%20people%20want%20you%20around%20and%20that%20your%20input%20is%20valued.%20When%20a%20manager%20asks%20a%20colleague%20for%20their%20opinion%2C%20it%20shows%20that%20their%20contribution%20is%20respected.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsking%20thoughtful%20questions%20demonstrates%20a%20desire%20to%20add%20value%20and%20be%20included%20in%20discussions.%20%3Cspan%3EAsk%20questions%20and%20be%20keen%20to%20learn%2C%20whether%20that's%20identifying%20shared%20interests%20or%20questioning%20internal%20processes%20to%20remove%20roadblocks%20and%20create%20opportunities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3